            "title": "Fredrik Lundberg Sells Final Shares in Investor After 25 Years - Di",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\">\n        \n                    Financier Fredrik Lundberg has sold his entire stake in the investment company Investor after more than 25 years as a shareholder, according to a report by Dagens industri.<br/><br/>The last 250,000 shares were divested in February. As a result, for the first time since at least the year 2000, the financier no longer holds any shares in the company, according to the ownership database Holdings.<br/><br/>At the end of 2024, the holding represented approximately 0.05 percent of the shares, valued at nearly half a billion kronor. The shares were owned through Lundberg's private company, Lunden Kapitalförvaltning.\n    \n    </div>",
