            "title": "Lithuania prosecutes five people over 2024 parcel blasts",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>VILNIUS, March 6 (Reuters) - Lithuania's deputy general prosecutor said on Friday he has initiated court proceedings against five persons over detonations of parcels carried by DHL and DPD in Europe in 2024.</p><p>\n              The suspects were citizens of Russia, Ukraine and Lithuania and were being accused of terrorism, Deputy General Prosecutor Arturas Urbelis told a press conference.</p><!-- Article --><p>\n              Lithuania's prosecution service and criminal police last year said the detonations of the parcels in Germany, Britain and Poland were organised and supervised by Russian citizens with ties to Russia's military intelligence.</p><p>\n              Security officials in Lithuania said in 2024 the four parcels were part of a test run for a Russian plot to trigger explosions on cargo flights to the United States.</p><p>\n               (Reporting by Andirus Sytas, writing by Stine Jacobsen, editing by Terje Solsvik)</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/lithuania-prosecutes-five-people-over-2024-parcel-blasts-ce7e5fd8db8cff21",
            "pub_date": "2026-03-06 19:32:29",
            "source": "marketscreener",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
        {
            "title": "Heidelberg Materials to Close Paderborn Cement Plant",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Nina Kienle </p><br/><p>\n  Heidelberg Materials said it would close a cement plant in west Germany due to a significant decline in cement sales driven by weak construction demand. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The German building materials group on Friday said a total of 53 employees would be affected by the closure of the Paderborn Cement Plant. </p><p>\n\n  Solutions are being developed, that include internal transfers to nearby sites within the company, Heidelberg Materials said. </p><p>\n\n  Open positions created through early retirement programs at neighboring cements plants are also being offered to the affected employees, it added. </p><p>\n\n  The closure only applies to the cement plant, while activities from subsidiary Mineralik, as well as operations of the local ready-mixed concrete plant will remain unchanged, the group said. </p><p>\n\n  The step is part of Heidelberg Material's optimization of its European production network, increasingly aligning its cement portfolio toward low-carbon products, it said. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Nina Kienle at nina.kienle@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  03-06-26 0626ET</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/heidelberg-materials-to-close-paderborn-cement-plant-ce7e5fd8db8cf027",
            "pub_date": "2026-03-06 19:32:30",
